— Cardinal Bellarmine, year 1615 during the trial of Galileo</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uceruleanruneguard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CeruleanRuneguard</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 210<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/16/01 2:22:38 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.perfectblueproductions.com/eric/small.jpg WIDTH=70 HEIGHT=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Little Request...</span><hr size=1> <br>
I will fully support Bush, in whatever decision he makes.  Up until 9/11 I didn't care for Bush one iota.  But, now I must admit he's just about the most fitting person for this situation.<br>
<br>
The charge that our military is ill-fitted to handle this is an exaggeration.<br>
<br>
If we do it right our military will be fine, coupled with a good campaign of economic propaganda.  Propaganda is an overly dramatic word, but that's basically what it will take.<br>
<br>
What won't work:<br>
Guerrilla tactics<br>
Diplomacy<br>
Sanctions<br>
Bombing from afar<br>
Surgical strikes<br>
<br>
We may use a variety of these to soften them up, but to break the back of a well funded organization you have to hit it at it's root... money.  That will take an invasion.  Bin Laden (if he's the target) is worth 200 million dollars - that's the prime reason he is such a threat, take away the money and he becomes a fanatic that can't cross the Atlantic.<br>
<br>
After we do this, we'll likely use our economic prowess to woo the populace.<br>
<br>
Listen to Colin Powell, Hugh Shelton, Bush, and Rumsfeld.. the hints are there.  They're planning something fairly massive.  "1 million reservists alerted" "40 billion dollars" "long term campaign" "Nato enacts article 5"<br>
<br>
Granted this goes presumes a lot.  I look forward to seeing what they've actually planned, I have no doubt it'll be comprehensive.<br>
<br>
Ceru <p><center> <a href="http://home.directlink.net/~khaz/sf"> <img src="http://www.perfectblueproductions.com/eric/cerulean3.jpg" border="0"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uvakra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vakra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 258<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/16/01 3:33:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Little Request...</span><hr size=1> I also was not a huge fan of Bush, but I feel he will do the right thing.<br>
<br>
I hope what you suggest is part of the plan, those ideas do sound a lot less violent than the &quot;Nuke em all&quot; that I see so often.  I realize that violence will undoubtedly occur and that bombing will most likely occur.  But I would rather see Bush use his brains more than our brawns.  We are a powerful nation, we can do this without becoming just as barbaric as the terrorists were.  And the main reason I feel Bush will do the right thing is because I have interpreted his speeches to mean that we will handle this with intelligence and as little violence as possible.  For now, that is all I ask for.<br>
<br>
